MEMORANDUM


Privileged and Confidential





To:      Jeffrey
Epstein


From:  John
Amerling            


Re:      Weekly
Progress Report                   




Date:   October
27, 2006        








The following is brief
summary of the material events of the past week:





·       
A design team meeting was held on Wednesday October 25,
2006 in New York :
the most significant developments of which were:





o       The CZM drawings for the Pool Expansion
were reviewed; several changes were made and the documents were to be posted to
the FTP website on Thursday.


o       A complete walk through of the house and
library designs was conducted and many questions and issues were raised for
further resolution.


o       A considerable amount of time was spent
on defining the interfaces among the specialty contractors selected by Molyneux
with the client’s approval and the balance of the team; there are many
issues including shop drawings and coordination of deliveries and installation;
RR is to work out a protocol..


o       The phasing plan was revised accordingly.


o       The schedule for production of CZM
drawings for the combined complex on Friday for filing Monday; they will be
overnighted Friday night.


o       A future design meeting  will be held in
three weeks.





·       
CZM filings for Phase I will be made Monday.


·       
The Pond 
 Bay estimate and contract
has been released to Mr. Indyke.


·       
Budgets for the Office will be released on Monday for
client review and scheduling and budgeting for all Phase I activities have been
initiated.


·       
A barge has been located and negotiations are on going
to procure it.


·       
About two man weeks have been expended in the past
week and we expect that the same out of effort will be expended over the next
week.
